  "body": "\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth version: `geth version`\r\n - Version: 1.10.3-stable\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX\r\n- ubuntu 12.04 LTS\r\n\r\nEnvironment: docker, vagrant, host os\r\n- native linux\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behavior\r\n\r\n```sh\r\napt-get install software-properties-common \r\nadd-apt-repository -y ppa:ethereum/ethereum \r\napt-get update \r\napt-get install ethereum\r\napt-get install geth\r\n```\r\nin console..\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ngeth attach ipc:/mnt/eth-blockchain/geth.ipc\r\n\r\nFatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix /mnt/eth-blockchain/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Error Logs\r\n```sh\r\nFatal: Unable to attach to remote geth: dial unix /mnt/eth-blockchain/geth.ipc: connect: no such file or directory\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo I tried to find file. \r\n```sh\r\n find / -name \"geth.ipc\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt shows nothing. \r\n\r\nWhat did I miss ?",
